-- Chelsea Defeats Rubin Kazan 3-1 in Europa League Quarterfinals
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-04-04T21:03:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-04/chelsea-defeats-rubin-kazan-3-1-in-europa-league-quarterfinals.html
Fernando Torres  scored two goals as
Chelsea defeated Rubin Kazan 3-1 in their Europa League soccer
quarterfinal opener.  Victor Moses also scored at  Stamford  Bridge in west London
as Chelsea takes a two-goal advantage into the return match in
Moscow on April 11.  Tottenham rallied for a 2-2 home draw with Basel, Benfica
beat Newcastle 3-1 and Fenerbahce defeated Lazio 2-0, scoring
both goals after Ogenyi Onazi was sent off for a second yellow
card. Basel, Newcastle and Lazio host the second legs, also in
seven days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  